------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
File & Directory Management
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ls — Lists files and directories in the current directory [shows hidden files "la"]
cd — Changes the current directory | cd /Downloads/ | cd .. to go back
pwd — Prints the full path of the current directory
cat — Show full file content
less — View file page by page
head — Show first lines of a file
tail — Show last lines of a file
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Networking 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ping — Test internet connection
curl — Make web requests | -I[Header] -O[Download]
wget — Download files from web
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Search & Text Processing
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
find — Searches for files and directories | find [location "/ ] -type [f] -name[file name] [hides permission errors "2>/dev/null"]
grep — Searches text inside files
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HASH
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sha256sum [FILE] 
string [FILE] 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
File Editing
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nano — Opens a simple terminal-based text editor
mkdir — Makes directory. 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Package Management (Debian/Ubuntu)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
apt update — Updates the package list
apt install — Installs a package
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
System Information
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
uname -a — full system 
cat /etc/os-release — OS version
whoami — Prints the currently logged-in user
ip address — Displays network interfaces and IP addresses
top — Show running processes
ps — Show process list
df -h — Show disk usage
free -h — Show memory usage
lscpu — CPU infomation
lsblk — List Disk Drives

gcc - compiles; c, c++, | gcc test.c -o test -w
chmod - runs executable


/etc/crontab — runs executables on a timer.
/etc/shadow — password hashes
/etc/passwd — user account infomation 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Output & Display
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
echo — Prints text or variables to the terminal
